The ''web'' spell was first introduced in the time of [[Netheril]], in [[-654 DR|3205 NY (âˆ’654 DR)]], under the name ''Shan's web'', after the [[arcanist]] [[Shan (arcanist)|Shan]]. It later became known simply as ''web''.

In the [[1357 DR|Year of the Prince, 1357 DR]], [[Kyriani Agrivar]] and [[Onyx the Invincible]] dueled the [[wizard]] [[Parwyyd Hanifar]] and his personal assistant [[Dunstanny]] outside the [[Great Door]]. Moving into a niche, Dunstanny suggested that Parwyyd employ a ''web'' over the entrance, anchored high and low with minimum depth. It soon trapped Kyri and Onyx like flies and ended the fight.{{Cite comic/The Ostus Legacy|13}}

''Web'' was commonly known and used by the magical community by [[1358 DR]]. It was one of the spells within ''[[Galadaster's Orizon]]''.
